==治療==<!--
Again this depends on oral bicarbonate supplementation. However, this will increase urinary bicarbonate wasting and may well promote a bicarbonate [[:wikt:diuresis|diuresis]]. The amount of bicarbonate given may have to be very large, to stay ahead of the urinary losses. Correction with oral [[bicarbonate|bicarbonate]] may exacerbate urinary potassium losses and precipitate [[hypokalemia|hypokalemia]].<ref>{{cite journal |author=Rodríguez Soriano J |title=Renal tubular acidosis: the clinical entity |journal=J. Am. Soc. Nephrol. |volume=13 |issue=8 |pages=2160–70 |year=2002 |pmid=12138150 |doi=10.1097/01.ASN.0000023430.92674.E5 |url=http://jasn.asnjournals.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=12138150}}</ref> As with dRTA, reversal of the chronic acidosis should reverse bone demineralization.<ref>{{cite journal |author=McSherry E |title=Renal tubular acidosis in childhood |journal=Kidney Int. |volume=20 |issue=6 |pages=799–809 |year=1981 |pmid=7038264 |doi=10.1038/ki.1981.213 |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_kidney-international_1981-12_20_6/page/799}}</ref>

[[Thiazide|Thiazide]] diuretics can also be used as treatment by making use of contraction alkalosis caused by them.-->

